Yeah that is a Olecranon Bursitis a elbow inflammation of the Bursa( latin for pocket/sack) this pocket contains synovial fluid to keep the joints nicely lubricated. When you overload your elbow (also very common on the knees) you body produce a lot of synovial fluid which is trapped in the bursa/pocket. The bump on it could be the firestarter  and if you sat a lot at the desk and rested the elbow joints on the desk, the joints/bursa got even more irritated which led to the inflammation and constant swelling. This condition is also called popeye elbow
